-! # how to errors: 001-comments-block-unterminated.zo
-!
-! @cmd: `zo build 001-comments-block-unterminated.zo`
-!
-! Block comments in Zo start with `-*` and end with `*-`. 
-!
-! If you forget to close one, the compiler eats everything after it — 
-! your entire program disappears into the comment. You are "Working 
-! Blind" because the code you see isn't actually being compiled.

-* This block comment never closes, so everything below is "dead."
fun main() {
  showln("Hello?");
}

-! ## the diagnostic map.
-!
-! Look at the arrows (╭─▶) in the expected output. Zo shows you exactly 
-! where the "hunger" started and how much of your file was swallowed. 
-! 
-! ## try this.
-!
-!   - close the comment by adding the closing marker at line 11.
-!   - run the program. suddenly, `fun main()` is "visible" to the
-!     compiler again.
-!   - can you nest block comments? try putting one inside another.

-- EXPECTED OUTPUT:
-- [E0002] Error: Unterminated block comment
--     ╭─[ 001-comments-block-unterminated.zo:11:1 ]
--     │
--  11 │ ╭─▶ -* This block comment never closes, so everything below is "dead."
--     ┆ ┆
--  37 │ ├─▶ -- ────╯
--     │ │
--     │ ╰───────────── here
-- ────╯